quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  46,29,"Recall when We dispatched towards you a number of jinn, to listen to the Quran. When they came in its presence, they said, “Pay attention!” Then, when it was concluded, they rushed to their people, warning them"
  46,30,"They said, “O our people, we have heard a Scripture, sent down after Moses, confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth, and to a straight path"
  46,31,"O our people! Answer the caller to God, and believe in Him; and He will forgive you your sins, and will save you from a painful punishment.”"
  46,32,"He who does not answer the caller to God will not escape on earth, and has no protectors besides Him. Those are in obvious error"
  46,33,"Do they not realize that God, who created the heavens and the earth, and was never tired by creating them, is Able to revive the dead? Yes indeed; He is Capable of everything"
  46,34,"On the Day when those who disbelieved are presented to the Fire: “Is this not real?” They will say, “Yes, indeed, by our Lord.” He will say, “Then taste the suffering for having disbelieved.”"
  46,35,"So be patient, as the messengers with resolve were patient, and do not be hasty regarding them. On the Day when they witness what they are promised, it will seem as if they had lasted only for an hour of a day. A proclamation: Will any be destroyed except the sinful people"